The LA Times frequently highlights several standout pizzerias across Southern California in its food 
coverage.  Their articles often mention well-known spots such as Pizzeria Mozza in Los Angeles, known
for its artisian crust and celebrity chef influence, and Apollonia's Pizzeria, famous for its thick, 
caramelized edge Detroit style pies.  They also regularly reference Prime Pizza, a popular New York
style slice shop with multiple LA locations, and DeSano Pizza Bakery, which focuses on traditional 
Neapolitan techniques.  Other restaurants that appear in their coverage include Gjelina in Venice for
its wood-fired approach, Hail Mary Pizza in Atwater Village for creative toppings, and Pizzana, which
blends modern techniques with classic Italian flavors. Overall, the LA Times tends to spotlight 
places that emphasize craftsmanship, high quality ingredients, and distinctive regional styles.